build a login component with angular front end and springboot backend using oauth based authentication for enterprise applications

**User Requirements**

* The user shall be able to log in to the application using their enterprise credentials.
* The user shall be able to see a list of all the applications they have access to.
* The user shall be able to launch any of the applications they have access to.

**Functional Requirements**

* The login component shall be implemented using Angular.
* The backend shall be implemented using Spring Boot.
* The application shall use OAuth 2.0 for authentication.
* The application shall use a centralized user directory for authentication.
* The application shall support single sign-on (SSO).
* The application shall support multi-factor authentication (MFA).

**Non-Functional Requirements**

* The application shall be scalable to support a large number of users.
* The application shall be highly available.
* The application shall be secure.
* The application shall be easy to use.
* The application shall be well-documented.

**Additional Requirements**

* The application shall be developed using agile development methodologies.
* The application shall be tested using automated testing tools.
* The application shall be deployed using continuous integration and continuous deployment (CI/CD) pipelines.
* The application shall be monitored using a centralized monitoring system.
* The application shall be supported by a dedicated support team.
